{"TopicId":191026,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Tesla Thread","CreatedByName":"GearsNSuch","CreatedById":190371,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-14T21:02:29Z","PageNum":13,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T00:35:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHertz makes an order for 100,000 Model 3\u0027s worth $4.3B, which is the largest EV order ever. That\u0027ll make the waiting list grow a bit longer...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6751436432\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Hertz/status/1452607992961064963?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:563px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T00:44:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd apparently Tesla is now worth $1T.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T01:01:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup\u2026 demand problem all right\u2026\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T06:14:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, finally got my FSD beta yesterday.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then lost it.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then got it again.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause apparently this happened:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed607615459\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1452729138758963203?s=21\u0022 style=\u0022height:764px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nBeta software gonna beta, but yeesh, it was dang near undrivable for a stretch there, FSD or no. And now that I\u2019ve had a couple drives with it\u2026 yeah, it\u2019s kinda like driving with a flustered 16 year old at the wheel.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wacko:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_wacko.png\u0022 title=\u0022:wacko:\u0022\u003E\u00A0This should be interesting.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut it does seem to have finally stopped diving into turn lanes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-07T16:12:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTesla opened a factory in Markham, Ontario, for making battery production equipment.\u00A0 With a factory dedicated to making battery manufacturing machinery, that (hopefully) means a LOT of battery production lines. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/tesla-open-canada-battery-gear-factory-markham-ontario-mayor-2021-11-05/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EReuters\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuilding the machine that builds the machines that build the machines....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-07T16:15:56Z\u0022 title=\u002211/07/2021 04:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 7, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jack White","CreatedById":216567,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-08T15:20:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224052281\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636301529\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTesla opened a factory in Markham, Ontario, for making battery production equipment.\u00A0 With a factory dedicated to making battery manufacturing machinery, that (hopefully) means a LOT of battery production lines. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/tesla-open-canada-battery-gear-factory-markham-ontario-mayor-2021-11-05/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EReuters\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuilding the machine that builds the machines that build the machines....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat, factories is a great way to improve battery production technologies.\u00A0 Even that sounds funny but we need machines that build the other machines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-24T21:25:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, Not really about Tesla, but since Tesla is pretty much synonymous with EV and there is no EV thread apparently, I\u0027ll just drop this here...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently Dodge, er, FCA is finally ready to get into the EV game...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xZNXVuzPio4?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-24T21:47:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224052567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636384843\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216567\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jack White\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/8/2021 at 4:20 PM, Jack White said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat, factories is a great way to improve battery production technologies.\u00A0 Even that sounds funny but we need machines that build the other machines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need factories to make the machines to make the machines who make the end product for now, later we will need much more layers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-24T22:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637790446\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need factories to make the machines to make the machines who make the end product for now, later we will need much more layers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-24T23:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637789109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently Dodge, er, FCA is finally ready to get into the EV game...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022better-late.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002241.53\u0022 height=\u0022250\u0022 width=\u0022602\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.chicagonow.com/cubs-den/files/2019/09/better-late.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe if they try \u003Cem\u003Ereally\u003C/em\u003E hard they can finally compete with the Model S\u2026 from 2012\u2026\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_dry.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-25T05:10:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637789109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTesla is pretty much synonymous with EV\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust 15% of total.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.statista.com/statistics/541390/global-sales-of-plug-in-electric-vehicle-manufacturers/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.statista.com/statistics/541390/global-sales-of-plug-in-electric-vehicle-manufacturers/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637790446\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need factories to make the machines to make the machines who make the end product for now, later we will need much more layers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHumans, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, to make humans.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-25T06:39:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224059064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637817051\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust 15% of total.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n21% once you subtract plug-in \u003Cem\u003Ehybrids\u003C/em\u003E, the next highest is VW with half that.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.investors.com/news/tesla-still-leads-global-ev-market-and-its-not-even-close/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.investors.com/news/tesla-still-leads-global-ev-market-and-its-not-even-close/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd something like 80% market share in the US.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022-_-\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_sleep.png\u0022 title=\u0022-_-\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-25T14:48:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, ther other EVs I see look like noise, and with few exceptions (Ford and Porsche) I instantly think, \u0022Why did you buy that instead of a Tesla?\u0022 And I think that of the Ford and Porsche, too, here in NM\u2014because taking them out for a drive almost anywhere outside ABQ means a long drive, and that\u0027s not even ideal for Teslas yet. My buddy took his X to his house in Durango a couple times, then gave up and takes his Audi instead because of supercharger availability (lack of) N of Santa Fe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-25T15:20:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224059135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637851694\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEVs \u0026lt;...\u0026gt; Porsche\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Elefant_USAOM-01.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.09\u0022 height=\u0022420\u0022 width=\u0022699\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/07/Elefant_USAOM-01.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-25T23:19:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, is Porche making an all-electric Tank Destroyer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-26T05:21:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224059314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637882354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022101988\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Rakaydos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, is Porche making an all-electric Tank Destroyer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, almost 80 years ago. But a hybrid one, of course.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elefant\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elefant\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"grungar3x7","CreatedById":145910,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-04T08:40:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224059378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637904117\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/26/2021 at 12:21 AM, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, almost 80 years ago. But a hybrid one, of course.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elefant\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elefant\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow, 6.5 liters per kilometer, highway.\u00A0 That\u0027s Petrol, not diesel as well...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-06T20:22:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/exclusive-sec-probes-tesla-over-whistleblower-claims-solar-panel-defects-2021-12-06/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/exclusive-sec-probes-tesla-over-whistleblower-claims-solar-panel-defects-2021-12-06/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-28T22:03:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/7_9aVzf5fC4?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis guy\u0027s Model S wouldn\u0027t work, and Tesla quoted him 20000 Euros to replace the entire battery assembly. Instead, he decided to blow it up with 30 kg of dynamite.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-12-28T22:06:44Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2021 10:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-19T16:14:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.msnbc.com/the-reidout/watch/elon-musk-s-car-company-tesla-faces-allegations-of-racist-discrimination-against-black-employees-133168709936\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.msnbc.com/the-reidout/watch/elon-musk-s-car-company-tesla-faces-allegations-of-racist-discrimination-against-black-employees-133168709936\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOuch\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Worth watching)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-19T21:33:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will add: this kind of sensational news is often one sided clickbait.\u00A0 Plaintiffs often overstate their cases in the hopes of a jury award... Although if true, they certainly state a claim for which relief should be granted.\u00A0 Which brings up the importance of the jury.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShrug - whether it even reaches a jury is kind of unlikely.\u00A0 Thing is that companies get sued all the time, sometimes with meritorious claims sometimes for utter nonsense, and the sad truth is that it is often cheaper to settle than prove innocence.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill be interesting to see how this pans out\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-19T22:15:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can google a specific type of bad claim about a workplace, sexism, racism, yada, yada, yada, and put in a company name of your choice, amazon, GM, BMW, tesla, etc\u2014and you will find they have been or are being sued by someone making that claim. Heck, works for national labs, too, not just their contractors. Welcome to American, the land of the frivolous lawsuit. Not every claim is frivolous, but the idea that Tesla has some intentional policy around this is utterly absurd. Individual workers are humans, and some humans are lousy, so sure. But all the incentive structures are for HR to stomp this, honestly to the point of over correction in many cases. Any claim that all outcome differences must have a systemic cause is religion, not reality, IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy cousin is quite well off via defending such claims in court (he\u0027s a defendant\u0027s attorney (partner) at a huge firm back east that does this nationally and internationally), and they have a list of clients that looks like the fortune 500.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-19T22:16:43Z\u0022 title=\u002202/19/2022 10:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 19, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by tater\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-19T22:32:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtraordinary claims require Extraordinary evidence.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022-_-\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_sleep.png\u0022 title=\u0022-_-\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-19T22:38:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224094007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221645309933\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257438\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CatastrophicFailure\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, CatastrophicFailure said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtraordinary claims require Extraordinary evidence.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022-_-\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_sleep.png\u0022 title=\u0022-_-\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndividual claims that some single event happened\u2014not extraordinary at all. Absolutely should involve some sort of follow up\u2014but any claim should \u003Cem\u003Erequire\u003C/em\u003E evidence.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClaims of a pattern or system of doing so needs proof at a higher level, since you need to prove it happened, and it was \u003Cem\u003Epolicy\u003C/em\u003E to happen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither are impossible to demonstrate in cases where it actually happened.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnything that happens at tesla gets huge press right now, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-20T01:01:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224093973\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221645306421\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlaintiffs often overstate their cases\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe US court system is based on an adversarial justice model. You are not ever supposed to make your opponents case for them. You present your own case as strongly as possible, and let the opponents defend themselves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}